A Rapid Response Team, RRT in “A” Division, Warri, Delta State, has arrested a 20-year-old boy, Aliyu Adamu, with 237 wraps of weed suspected to Indian hemp. The suspect, who has confessed to the crime, was arrested based on intelligence, DAILY POST gathered. The Delta State Police Command led by CP Ari Muhammed Ali, disclosed this in a terse statement signed by the Acting Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe. He said, “Suspect allegedly confessed to be a major dealer in Indian Hemp. Investigation is ongoing.”